## Milestone 2 — Data Bootstrapping & Stores (Week 1–2)

**Goal:** Wire static JSON data for one region, one boss, a handful of runes and items; set up Zustand stores.

### Tasks
- [x] Create `public/data/` JSON files with minimal entries:
  - [x] `regions.json` → 1 region: `region_edo_streets` with 3–4 nodes (camp, shrine, boss).
  - [x] `enemies.json` → 2 enemies: `enemy_ronin`, `enemy_city_guard`.
  - [x] `bosses.json` → 1 boss: `boss_oni_general` with 2 phases and loot table.
  - [x] `runes.json` → 2 skill runes, 2 link runes.
  - [x] `weapons.json` → 2 starter katanas.
  - [x] `armors.json`, `accessories.json` → 2–3 items each.
  - [x] `passiveNodes.json` → small web of ~10 nodes.
- [x] Implement `store/usePlayerStore.ts`:
  - [x] Base character stats, level, EXP, resource, HP.
  - [x] Starting two skill runes and one katana equipped.
- [x] Implement `store/useInventoryStore.ts`:
  - [x] Equipped slots, bag items.
- [x] Implement `store/useRuneStore.ts`:
  - [x] Owned runes, 4 skill slots, equip/unequip actions.
- [x] Implement `store/useMapStore.ts`:
  - [x] Current region/node, discovered/cleared nodes, idle farming state.
- [x] Implement `store/useChapterStore.ts`:
  - [x] Completed chapters, killed bosses, dialogue flags.
- [x] Implement `store/useOfflineStore.ts`:
  - [x] Last online timestamp, pending EXP/materials.

### Exit criteria
- [x] JSON files load successfully at runtime (e.g. via simple debug screen).
- [x] Stores can be inspected via React DevTools / logs (no UI yet).
- [x] You can log out: "Current region: Edo Streets, Node: Market Camp, Player Lv.1 with Katana + 2 skill runes."

